FIX 1: app/doctor/earnings.tsx (2 errors)
----------------------------------------------------------------
  ERROR:  TS2304 — Cannot find name 'allTotal' (lines 141, 175)
  CAUSE:  `allTotal` is a local variable inside the `load()` async
          callback (line 52). It goes out of scope after `load()`
          finishes. The JSX render tried to reference it directly
          instead of using the `totalAllTime` state variable that
          receives the same value via `setTotalAllTime(allTotal)`
          on line 105.
  FIX:    Replaced `allTotal` → `totalAllTime` in both JSX locations.
          - Line 141: Summary card "All Time" display
          - Line 175: Breakdown section "Total Revenue" display

----------------------------------------------------------------
FIX 2: app/doctor/patient-info.tsx (1 error)
----------------------------------------------------------------
  ERROR:  TS2345 — Argument of type 'never[] | { xrays: string[];
          treatmentPlans: string[]; photos: string[] }' is not
          assignable to parameter of type 'SetStateAction<any[]>'
  CAUSE:  `getPatientFiles()` returns an object with xrays,
          treatmentPlans, photos fields — NOT an array. But
          the state was typed as `useState<any[]>([])`, causing
          a type mismatch on `setFiles(f || [])`.
          Additionally, the seed data stores numeric counts
          ({xrays: 2, ...}) while the type signature declares
          string arrays ({xrays: string[], ...}).
  FIX:    - Changed state type: `useState<any[]>([])` → `useState<any>(null)`
          - Changed setter: `setFiles(f || [])` → `setFiles(f)`
          - Changed display (line 143): `files.length` → computed
            count that handles both number values (seed data) and
            array values (real upload data) via Object.values reduce.

----------------------------------------------------------------
FIX 3: app/patient/clinic-map.tsx (1 error)
----------------------------------------------------------------
  ERROR:  TS2749 — 'MapView' refers to a value, but is being
          used as a type here.
  CAUSE:  MapView is conditionally assigned at runtime:
            let MapView: any = View;
            if (Platform.OS !== "web") { MapView = Maps.default; }
          This makes MapView a value (variable), not a type.
          `useRef<MapView>` tries to use it as a generic type
          parameter, which TypeScript rejects.
  FIX:    Changed `useRef<MapView>(null)` → `useRef<any>(null)`.
          This is appropriate since MapView is already typed as
          `any` and the ref is only used for `.animateToRegion()`.

